<taxonomicName authorityName=", Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2006" box="[690,874,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricornis">
<emphasis box="[690,874,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">N. quadricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration, but is readily distinguished by the distinctive aedeagus. The specific name refers to the Mexican state where the 
<typeStatus box="[1064,1114,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected.
